  "read": "TileLang query-major compact partial producer. This is a concrete reduced-write dKV kernel: it accumulates by precomputed active compressed-group slot inside the CTA, and writes compact partial rows instead of one selected row per token/topk pair. scalar_reduced is the working compact-row/writeback gate; mfma_reduced is the intended TileLang GEMM contribution body and currently tests the MI350 lowering path. It uses diagnostic materialized probs and grad_logits; QK/PV recompute is intentionally outside this gate. This run folds the compact partial rows into final [groups, D] dKV with a TileLang panel-dense no-atomic reducer inside the timed callable. The reducer owns one final compressed group row and D block, then sums that group's compact partial rows across token tiles. It is target-shape specific and requires dense panel_capacity_random compact-row layout.",
